The Democratic Alliance (DA) seems to be their own worst enemy and no one else should be blamed for their apparent dismal state but themselves. Just over three years ago, the party was doing well. Under their first black leader Mmusi Maimane, the party managed to win three metropolitan municipalities aside from retaining their Republic of Europe, Cape Town. They tried to prove they’re a non-racial party by placing black men – Herman Mashaba and Solly Msimanga – as mayors of Johannesburg and Tshwane respectively. They handed out title deeds, cut ribbons, implemented Expanded Public Works Programmes and did some...